I"v<p>Working on the GraphQL API’s website today, and I decided I wanted to have some animated stats on the page.</p>

<p>Basically to show how many establishments we hold data on and how many users we have using the API etc. I thought it would be a nice addition to the site.</p>

<p>So i created a simple JS function which i could call rather than relying on ones that are already out there. That said, i may move to using something like <a href="https://inorganik.github.io/countUp.js/">inorganik’s countUp</a>, but we shall see how this simple script works out.</p>

<h2 class="number text-green">100</h2>
<h2 class="number text-green">550001</h2>
<h2 class="number text-green">8425</h2>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>function countUp(numberElement) {
  let current = 0;
  const total = parseInt(numberElement.textContent);
  const increment = Math.ceil(total / 100);

  function step() {
    current += increment;
    if (current &gt; total) current = total;
    numberElement.textContent = current.toLocaleString();
    (current !== total) &amp;&amp; requestAnimationFrame(step);
  }
  step();
}

document.querySelectorAll('.number').forEach(elem =&gt; countUp(elem));
</code></pre></div></div>

